<https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/defence-nuclear-safety-committee> <http://ogp.me/ns#description> "The Defence Nuclear Safety Expert Committee (DNSEC) is a public body classified as an Expert Committee. Its purpose is to be a key source of independent advice to the Ministry of Defence. It bases its advice on its scrutiny of the available evidence of safety arrangements across the Defence Nuclear Enterprise. DNSEC works with the Ministry of Defence ."@en .
